wikipedia_page.main: Francesco Ticciati (20 December 1893 – 10 February 1949) was an Italian composer, concert pianist, piano teacher and lecturer.

response: ** Francesco Ticciati, Italian composer, pianist, teacher and lecturer (b. 1893)
*Died: Francesco Ticciati, 55, Italian composer and concert pianist

The Ticciati family has continued to be associated with the arts; the pianist and composer Francesco Ticciati (1893–1949), composer and arranger Niso Ticciati (1924–1972) and in the present day: the designer Giovanna Ticciati, the violinist Hugo Ticciati and his brother the conductor Robin Ticciati.
*Francesco Ticciati (1893–1949), Italian composer, concert pianist, piano teacher and lecturer
